ldir command

    (A)  FUNCTION
         Ldir command shows the contents of specified directory in
         native file system.

    (B)  SYNOPSIS

         ldir  { <pathname> }

    (C)  PARAMETERS
         <pathname>
           specifies the pathname to the directory which should follow
           the rules of native file system.
           Current working directory of SECONDS' process is specified
           if no <pathname> is given.

    (D)  NOTES
         Ldir command does not recognize any wildcard.

    (E)  SEE ALSO
         exec command
         dir command



